---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Background, engineering philosophy, and capabilities.">
  <section class="py-12 max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">About</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-foreground-muted leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I'm a software engineer focused on building well-structured systems that
        communicate clearly — both in how they work and how they're presented.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8">Engineering Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        I believe the best engineering work is defined by clarity of structure,
        consistency of execution, and alignment between documentation and
        implementation. Systems should be easy to understand, easy to maintain,
        and built with intention.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8">Capabilities</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Software architecture and system design</li>
        <li>Infrastructure and cloud platform engineering</li>
        <li>Technical documentation and communication</li>
        <li>Full-stack development with modern tooling</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8">Approach</h2>
      <p>
        Every project on this platform is treated as a real system — with
        architecture documentation, clear design decisions, and structured
        implementation. This reflects how I work in practice, not just in
        portfolio settings.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
